      <h2>About Mental Health Awareness</h2>
      <p>Mental health affects how we think, feel, and act. Raising awareness reduces stigma and encourages people to seek help when needed.</p>
      <p>Key facts:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>1 in 4 people experience a mental health issue in their lifetime (WHO).</li>
        <li>Depression and anxiety are the most common.</li>
        <li>Early support improves outcomes.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Tips for better mental health:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Practice mindfulness or meditation.</li>
        <li>Stay connected with loved ones.</li>
        <li>Exercise and eat balanced meals.</li>
        <li>Prioritize sleep and self-care.</li>
      </ul>
